msContents.summary: Commentary on the Zīj-i jadīd-i Sultānī, which comprised tables of calendar calculations, trigonometry, planets, and stars compiled from observations made at the observatory in Samarqand, completed in 1447. Includes some tables, marginal commentary attributed to Mullah Muẓaffar (f. 239v), 7 generally contemporary diagrams tipped in, and 1 diagram and 1 small note laid in.

msItem.title: Sharḥ-i Zīj-i jadīd-i Sultānī
msItem.author: Birjandī, ʻAbd al-ʻAlī ibn Muḥammad ibn Ḥusayn, 16th cent

supportDesc.extent: 242 leaves : 244 x 174 (190 x 130) mm. bound to 247 x 186 mm. +
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, ii + 242; [1-11, i, 12-63, i, 64-85, i, 86-87, i, 88-130, i, 131-220, i, 221-230, i, 231-242], modern foliation in pencil, upper left recto. Catchwords on each leaf, lower left verso.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq script by the author, with marginal commentary in the hand of Mullah Muẓaffar (f. 239v).

decoDesc.decoNote: Numerous diagrams and some tables in red and black ink; 2 marginal diagrams in green ink (f. 209r); overlining in red throughout.

binding.p: Later morocco; some notes and diagrams in margins show signs of trimming.

origin.p: Written in Persia, now Iran, between 1523 (when the commentary was completed) and 1528 (when the author died).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Prince Sadruddin Aga Khan; sold at auction as part of his collection at Piasa (Paris), 7 June 1999.
Sold by Sam Fogg Ltd. (London) to Lawrence J. Schoenberg, Mar 2001.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2011.
